{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.22",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 22,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 22",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 22 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:1",
      "text": "Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:2",
      "text": "Can a man be profitable unto God, as he that is wise may be profitable unto himself?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:3",
      "text": "Is it any pleasure to the Almighty, that thou art righteous? or is it gain to him, that thou makest thy ways perfect?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:4",
      "text": "Will he reprove thee for fear of thee? will he enter with thee into judgment?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:5",
      "text": "Is not thy wickedness great? and thine iniquities infinite?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:6",
      "text": "For thou hast taken a pledge from thy brother for nought, and stripped the naked of their clothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:7",
      "text": "Thou hast not given water to the weary to drink, and thou hast withholden bread from the hungry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:8",
      "text": "But as for the mighty man, he had the earth; and the honourable man dwelt in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:9",
      "text": "Thou hast sent widows away empty, and the arms of the fatherless have been broken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:10",
      "text": "Therefore snares are round about thee, and sudden fear troubleth thee;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:11",
      "text": "Or darkness, that thou canst not see; and abundance of waters cover thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:12",
      "text": "Is not God in the height of heaven? and behold the height of the stars, how high they are!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:13",
      "text": "And thou sayest, How doth God know? can he judge through the dark cloud?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:14",
      "text": "Thick clouds are a covering to him, that he seeth not; and he walketh in the circuit of heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:15",
      "text": "Hast thou marked the old way which wicked men have trodden?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:16",
      "text": "Which were cut down out of time, whose foundation was overflown with a flood:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:17",
      "text": "Which said unto God, Depart from us: and what can the Almighty do for them?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:18",
      "text": "Yet he filled their houses with good things: but the counsel of the wicked is far from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:19",
      "text": "The righteous see it, and are glad: and the innocent laugh them to scorn.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:20",
      "text": "Whereas our substance is not cut down, but the remnant of them the fire consumeth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:21",
      "text": "Acquaint now thyself with him, and be at peace: thereby good shall come unto thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:22",
      "text": "Receive, I pray thee, the law from his mouth, and lay up his words in thine heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:23",
      "text": "If thou return to the Almighty, thou shalt be built up, thou shalt put away iniquity far from thy tabernacles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:24",
      "text": "Then shalt thou lay up gold as dust, and the gold of Ophir as the stones of the brooks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:25",
      "text": "Yea, the Almighty shall be thy defence, and thou shalt have plenty of silver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:26",
      "text": "For then shalt thou have thy delight in the Almighty, and shalt lift up thy face unto God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:27",
      "text": "Thou shalt make thy prayer unto him, and he shall hear thee, and thou shalt pay thy vows.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:28",
      "text": "Thou shalt also decree a thing, and it shall be established unto thee: and the light shall shine upon thy ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:29",
      "text": "When men are cast down, then thou shalt say, There is lifting up; and he shall save the humble person.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.22.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:30",
      "text": "He shall deliver the island of the innocent: and it is delivered by the pureness of thine hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
